# CVE-2026-33671 — picomatch <4.0.4 ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns.
#
# The flagged copy is the picomatch bundled inside the Node base image's own
# npm CLI (/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/picomatch), NOT our app
# dependencies — our package-lock.json pins picomatch 4.0.4 / 2.3.2 (both clean).
#
# It is only reachable if npm itself parses attacker-controlled glob patterns,
# which the production container never does (it runs `next start`). No runtime
# exposure.
#
# Remove this entry once the node:22-alpine base image ships an npm whose
# bundled picomatch is >= 4.0.4 (then a rebuild clears it on its own).
CVE-2026-33671
